│ instruction has a MemoryAccess, then the cloned instruction should also     │
│ have one. However, this assumption can be wrong in cases where the original │
│ instruction was processed by a previous pass that incorrectly created a     │
│ MemoryAccess for a non-memory-touching instruction, or when the instruction │
│ itself doesn't actually touch memory. The safer approach is to check if the │
│ instruction actually touches memory before creating a MemoryAccess. Let me  │
│ modify the condition to also check if the instruction may read from or      │
│ write to memory.                                                            │
